
[1]calamity

   CALAMITY, n. Any great misfortune, or cause of misery; generally
   applied to events or disasters which produce extensive evils, as loss
   of crops, earthquakes, conflagrations, defeat of armies, and the like.
   But it is applied also to the misfortunes which bring great distress
   upon individuals.

   The deliberations of calamity are rarely wise.
